This paper deals with energy-efficient scheduling strategies for small cell networks in 5G wireless networks. The paper focuses on analyzing the statistics of the overall network traffic and proposes load-based on/off scheduling algorithms. This work involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography (cs.CR) as it deals with optimizing the energy efficiency of wireless networks while maintaining the network throughput and delay tolerance.
